The paper deals with the problem of image classification, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves kernel methods and similarity measures, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses experiments on public datasets, which are often used in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
